quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  5,27,"And recite to them the true story of the two sons of Adam, when they both offered an offering, but it was accepted from one of them and was not accepted from the other (who) said, \"I will definitely kill you.\" (The other) said, \"God accepts only from those who guard (against evil)"
  5,28,"if you stretch your hand towards me to kill me I will not stretch my hand towards you to kill you, I fear God the Lord of the worlds"
  5,29,I intend that you should bear my sin as well as your own sin so that you should be among the inhabitants of hell and that is the reward of the unjust
  5,30,"So his soul willed for him, the murder of his brother, he thus killed him and thereby became one of the losers"
  5,31,"Then God sent a crow scratching the earth to show him how to hide his brother's dead body. He said, \"Sorrowful is my state, was I unable to be equal even to this crow so as to hide the dead body of my brother?\" He thus became one of those who regret"
  5,32,"For that reason, We prescribed for the children of Israel that whoever kills anyone without (it being a killing of the murderer of) someone, or due to corruption in the earth, then it will be as if he killed all human beings; and whoever saves a life then it will be as if he saved the lives of all human beings. And Our messengers had come to them with clear proofs, then even after that many of them are committers of excesses in the earth"
  5,33,"Indeed, the penalty for those who wage war against God and His Messenger and spread terrorism in the land is death, crucifixion, cutting off their hands and feet on opposite sides, or exile from the land. This ˹penalty˺ is a disgrace for them in this world, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment in the Hereafter"
  5,34,"except those who repent before you overpower them*, so know that God is Protectively Forgiving, Merciful"
  5,35,O you who believe ! fear God and seek the means of approach to Him and strive in His way so as to be successful
  5,36,"As for those who do not believe, even if all that is in the earth were theirs and the like of it with it(Double), to give as ransom for the punishment on the day of resurrection, it will certainly not be accepted from them and for them there will be a painful punishment"
  5,37,They will intend to come out of the fire but they will not be able to come out of it and for them there will be a lasting punishment
  5,38,"And the male thief and the female thief, cut off their hands, a reward for that which they earned, an exemplary punishment from God, and God is Mighty, Wise"
  5,39,"But whoever repents after his injustice and amends, then God will turn to him (mercifully), God is certainly Protectively Forgiving, Merciful"
  5,40,"Do you not know that God's is the kingdom of the skies and the earth, He punishes whom He wills and He protectively forgives whom He wills, and God has power over everything"